        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 3:43PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 343 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southeast of Starkey, or 17 miles southwest of La Grande,
moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Starkey.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
